WEBVTT

00:01.802 --> 00:03.304
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Whassup, peeps? You'll recall
 our favorite virgin mother

00:03.337 --> 00:04.305
just heard this bombshell.

00:04.338 --> 00:06.140
Rose is dead.

00:06.174 --> 00:08.276
She can't ever hurt
 you or Mateo.

00:08.309 --> 00:09.710
I couldn't jeopardize
your safety again.

00:09.743 --> 00:11.312
I had to push you away--
 but it's over now.

00:11.345 --> 00:12.380
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Not as thrilled

00:12.413 --> 00:14.148
about Sin Rostro's death--

00:14.182 --> 00:16.184
her former lover, Luisa,

00:16.216 --> 00:18.219
AKA Rafael's sister--
 see, she'd stayed

00:18.252 --> 00:20.654
in contact with Rose...
LUISA: I'm an addict.

00:20.688 --> 00:23.257
I was obsessed-- I just
couldn't let her go.

00:23.291 --> 00:24.725
You should leave.
 And Rafael wasn't

00:24.758 --> 00:26.260
the only one who was bothered

00:26.294 --> 00:27.595
by their relationship.
I can't.

00:27.628 --> 00:30.231
In Luisa's defense,
 breakups are hard--

00:30.264 --> 00:33.101
as Zo and Ro were learning.

00:33.134 --> 00:34.502
I don't want to have
any more kids.

00:34.535 --> 00:36.237
And I know
you want them.

00:36.270 --> 00:39.140
Babies, man-- they're no joke.

00:39.173 --> 00:40.508
Which brings us to Petra.

00:40.541 --> 00:42.843
You see,
 she inseminated herself

00:42.876 --> 00:44.345
with Rafael's sperm
 because she thought

00:44.378 --> 00:45.279
they were meant to be together

00:45.313 --> 00:46.680
Crazy, right?

00:46.714 --> 00:48.782
But he did say he'd be there.

00:48.816 --> 00:50.784
(screams)
 Oh, and speaking of crazy,

00:50.818 --> 00:53.587
all this crime stuff has
 been bad for hotel business.

00:53.621 --> 00:56.457
Can't blame honeymooners for
 avoiding the Marbella, right?

00:56.490 --> 00:58.326
And on the topic
 of honeymooners,

00:58.359 --> 01:01.762
let's get back
 to our love story, shall we?

01:01.795 --> 01:04.197
When Jane Gloriana Villanueva

01:04.232 --> 01:08.436
was exactly 24 years,
 eight months and 17 days old,

01:08.469 --> 01:11.339
she had the most romantic night
 of her life.

01:11.372 --> 01:13.374
Don't think-- just tell me,
do you still love me?

01:13.407 --> 01:15.876
Yes.

01:15.909 --> 01:17.511
It also happened to be
 last night.

01:17.545 --> 01:19.680
Yes?
Yes.

01:19.713 --> 01:21.115
Oh...

01:22.616 --> 01:24.618
*

01:24.652 --> 01:27.321
Does this mean we can be
Facebook friends again?

01:27.355 --> 01:28.689
(laughs): Yes!

01:28.722 --> 01:30.758
I can't believe
you unfriended me.

01:30.791 --> 01:33.461
I had to.
I stalked your girlfriend.

01:33.494 --> 01:36.297
As for what happened next...
That was not
my girlfriend.

01:36.330 --> 01:38.299
We work together.
Your mom is crazy.

01:38.332 --> 01:39.733
Oh...

01:39.767 --> 01:42.403
What about you?
Did you date anyone?

01:42.436 --> 01:43.571
Well, I...

01:43.604 --> 01:45.173
Kinda. Yeah.

01:45.206 --> 01:46.407
My professor.

01:46.440 --> 01:48.809
Well, after exactly
 216 days apart,

01:48.842 --> 01:51.445
they had a lot to catch up on.

01:51.479 --> 01:52.646
He's huge!

01:52.680 --> 01:54.382
The professor?

01:54.415 --> 01:55.783
(relieved sigh)
Oh... Mateo.

01:55.816 --> 01:57.318
JANE:
It's giving me panic attacks.

01:57.351 --> 01:58.919
He lost his baby face.

01:58.952 --> 02:01.455
Well, pretty sure you're
looking at a baby right now.

02:01.489 --> 02:03.191
(laughs)

02:03.224 --> 02:05.326
(laughing): And then
I challenged McBaskets

02:05.359 --> 02:07.328
to a one-on-one.
Final score?

02:07.361 --> 02:08.696
56 to nothing.
Ooh.

02:08.729 --> 02:10.497
It was a lot closer
than you think.

02:10.531 --> 02:12.500
I almost scored
a bunch of times.

02:12.533 --> 02:14.168
JANE:
 No.

02:14.202 --> 02:16.470
I'msorry.

02:16.504 --> 02:18.506
Yeah, it was awful.

02:18.539 --> 02:19.807
I mean, N...

02:19.840 --> 02:22.376
Nadine died trying to save me.

02:22.410 --> 02:24.345
I can't believe it.
It's because I
didn't trust her.

02:24.378 --> 02:26.647
That's... what haunts me.

02:26.680 --> 02:29.517
I didn't trust her.
JANE:
 Trust me, I was shocked.

02:29.550 --> 02:31.819
And then when the
green card came...

02:31.852 --> 02:33.654
How much crying?

02:33.687 --> 02:35.689
So much crying.

02:36.957 --> 02:39.293
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 Come on,

02:39.327 --> 02:42.763
conversation wasn't the only
 thing they had to catch up on.

02:44.232 --> 02:46.500
MICHAEL:
This doesn't feel real.

02:46.534 --> 02:48.302
I know.

02:48.336 --> 02:49.903
But it was.

02:49.937 --> 02:53.307
Just the two of them,
 in their own little bubble.

02:53.341 --> 02:55.509
But we do need to talk
about Rafael.

02:55.543 --> 02:56.710
(bubble pops)

02:56.744 --> 02:58.579
*

03:04.418 --> 03:07.288
I have to apologize.
That's all.

03:07.321 --> 03:09.390
What happened
when I punched him--

03:09.423 --> 03:11.392
I think about that
every day.
 True, for the record.

03:11.425 --> 03:14.528
And I think about how angry
I was, and why...

03:14.562 --> 03:16.297
Rafael had gotten him fired.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.766
...and none of it matters.
I was wrong.

03:18.799 --> 03:21.669
So I just want to apologize
and start fresh.

03:21.702 --> 03:22.836
Great.

03:22.870 --> 03:24.872
But you gotta let me
talk to him first.

03:24.905 --> 03:26.474
And you should
really get going.

03:26.507 --> 03:28.542
Are you kicking me out?
(laughs): No.

03:28.576 --> 03:31.479
My mom and my grandma are
gonna wake up soon, and...

03:31.512 --> 03:33.781
I just don't want to deal
with their opinions yet.

03:33.814 --> 03:37.685
I think it might be
a little too late for that.

03:37.718 --> 03:40.220
*

03:42.690 --> 03:43.724
That's it?

03:43.757 --> 03:44.958
JANE (laughs):
Yes.

03:44.992 --> 03:47.261
We talked.
That's it.

03:47.295 --> 03:48.696
Your mom is a liar.

03:48.729 --> 03:50.631
Ma, don't say
that to him!

03:50.664 --> 03:51.999
Check me out.

03:53.434 --> 03:54.635
Ooh...

03:54.668 --> 03:56.537
Ah...
Wait for it.

03:56.570 --> 03:58.406
It still fits.

03:58.439 --> 03:59.907
I'm actually really excited

03:59.940 --> 04:01.775
to be picking up
a few shifts.
You're seriously trying

04:01.809 --> 04:03.711
to talk to me about
waitressing right now?

04:03.744 --> 04:06.514
What's going on! Are you
back together or not?

04:10.083 --> 04:11.785
Thank you, Abuela.

04:14.988 --> 04:16.757
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 ¿Y tú, Abuela?

04:16.790 --> 04:19.593
Look, as much as I want to
tell you how amazing it was...

04:19.627 --> 04:21.060
So it was amazing.

04:21.094 --> 04:22.663
...I need to talk
to Rafael first.

04:22.696 --> 04:24.798
He and Michael...

04:24.832 --> 04:26.600
I mean, they fought.

04:26.634 --> 04:28.902
I need to make sure that
they can coexist for Mateo.

04:28.936 --> 04:30.371
But don't worry,

04:30.404 --> 04:32.806
I will be talking to him
right away.

04:32.840 --> 04:33.841
(knocking on door)

04:35.042 --> 04:36.910
No, that's Rogelio.

04:36.944 --> 04:38.779
I, um, invited him
to breakfast.

04:38.812 --> 04:40.781
To remind you:
 it's been exactly

04:40.814 --> 04:43.617
12 hours and 41 minutes since
 Xiomara and Rogelio broke up.

04:43.651 --> 04:46.654
XIOMARA: I told you,
you don't have to knock.

04:46.687 --> 04:48.822
You can just come in and out
like you did before.

04:48.856 --> 04:51.325
Thank you. I just wanted
to be respectful.

04:51.359 --> 04:52.726
Mm-hmm.

04:54.695 --> 04:56.664
What?
JANE: Nothing.
I just don't think

04:56.697 --> 04:58.399
we expected you guys
to be so comfortable

04:58.432 --> 04:59.500
with each other
after the breakup.

04:59.533 --> 05:01.369
We decided to be mature
about this.

05:01.402 --> 05:03.504
Exactly. Like my good
friends Gwynnie and Chris,

05:03.537 --> 05:06.106
we have chosen to
consciously uncouple.
But we're not calling it that.

05:06.139 --> 05:07.575
Oh, yes,
we definitely are.

05:09.610 --> 05:11.479
I might be on the board
of Goop, Alba, so yes,

05:11.512 --> 05:12.913
I would say we're
very good friends.

05:12.946 --> 05:14.382
The point is,
we're bypassing

05:14.415 --> 05:15.516
all the negativity

05:15.549 --> 05:17.451
and going straight
to the friendship.

05:17.485 --> 05:18.952
ROGELIO: Exactly.
You're still accompanying me

05:18.986 --> 05:20.588
to the Tiago premiere, right?

05:20.621 --> 05:23.491
Of course.
I already RSVP'd to Paola.

05:23.524 --> 05:25.526
I should check in
on her, actually.

05:27.895 --> 05:30.498
We want to get
a hashtag trending
during the premiere.

05:30.531 --> 05:32.766
Have I told you guys
she used to work for J. Lo?

05:32.800 --> 05:34.568
Sí.
Yes.
Yes. Like, a couple of times.

05:34.602 --> 05:36.504
Like, I remember,
the last time you told me
Yeah. We heard.

05:36.537 --> 05:37.905
was just this morning
on the phone.
Yeah. That's right.

05:37.938 --> 05:38.939
Yep.
You texted it

05:38.972 --> 05:40.040
to me yesterday.

05:40.073 --> 05:41.575
Anyway, what I love about her

05:41.609 --> 05:43.577
is that she won't reveal
a single secret.

05:43.611 --> 05:47.481
Which is... also what I hate
about her. (chuckles)

05:52.520 --> 05:53.821
JANE:
And I have to go.

05:53.854 --> 05:56.123
And I'm really impressed
by the way you two

05:56.156 --> 05:57.658
are handling
the breakup.

05:59.727 --> 06:00.794
Bye.

06:00.828 --> 06:03.597
MAN: Rediscover the romance,
 and the magic,

06:03.631 --> 06:05.433
at the Marbella.

06:05.466 --> 06:07.568
It's a slice of heaven.

06:07.601 --> 06:08.969
Or hell.

06:09.002 --> 06:11.505
The Marbella Hotel.

06:11.539 --> 06:13.574
You check in,
but you never check out.

06:13.607 --> 06:15.576
Okay, seriously?
This is now the first thing

06:15.609 --> 06:17.010
that comes up
when you Google us?

06:17.044 --> 06:19.046
Yes! It has
half a million hits.

06:19.079 --> 06:21.181
(sighs)
I've made a call
to our marketing people

06:21.214 --> 06:23.451
and asked them to brainstorm
new ad campaign ideas.

06:23.484 --> 06:24.918
You think that's
necessary?

06:24.952 --> 06:27.087
Only if you want
to continue having guests.

06:27.120 --> 06:29.757
Yes, it's necessary!
And I want it done this week!

06:29.790 --> 06:31.692
Whoa. Why so soon?
I don't know, Rafael.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.661
You know, maybe just knowing
that two actual human beings

06:33.694 --> 06:36.096
are about to blast
out of my body at any moment

06:36.129 --> 06:38.732
has give me a sense of urgency.
Okay, first of all,

06:38.766 --> 06:41.435
"blast" out of your body?

06:41.469 --> 06:43.437
Wow.
Look, I just mean
there's a lot

06:43.471 --> 06:45.706
I want to get done before then--
I made a list.

06:45.739 --> 06:46.907
Ah.

06:46.940 --> 06:48.542
What?

06:48.576 --> 06:49.877
This happened with Jane.

06:49.910 --> 06:51.745
It's called nesting.

06:51.779 --> 06:53.614
It's when an expectant
mother becomes obsessed

06:53.647 --> 06:55.616
with planning out
all the details.

06:55.649 --> 06:58.619
Feathering her nest,
so to speak.

06:58.652 --> 07:01.455
In anticipation
of the baby.

07:01.489 --> 07:03.991
Are you serious
with that crap?

07:04.024 --> 07:07.695
Ask me what's on my list!

07:07.728 --> 07:10.498
What's on your list?
Night nurse interviews,
finalizing the nursery plans,

07:10.531 --> 07:12.633
and making a new
non-throat-slashing commercial

07:12.666 --> 07:13.734
for the Marbella!

07:13.767 --> 07:14.802
Got it.

07:14.835 --> 07:15.769
I'm on it.

07:15.803 --> 07:16.870
All of it.

07:16.904 --> 07:18.138
Thank you.

07:18.171 --> 07:20.040
(woman screams on video)

07:20.073 --> 07:22.710
MAN:
 Our luxurious honeymoon suites
 are to die for.

07:22.743 --> 07:23.711
(Lina shrieks)

07:23.744 --> 07:25.145
I can't believe it!

07:25.178 --> 07:26.747
(laughter)

07:26.780 --> 07:28.148
Oh. (gasps)
(gasps)

07:28.181 --> 07:31.118
You just made my job a
thousand percent more fun.

07:31.151 --> 07:33.120
Oh, it's nice to be back.
(sighs)

07:33.153 --> 07:34.822
It's familiar, you know?

07:34.855 --> 07:37.057
It's, like, my old life...
Yeah. So quick update.

07:37.090 --> 07:39.693
Mm.
We no longer hate
Busboy Ben.

07:39.727 --> 07:41.895
Uh-huh.
Turns out he was just
in a bad relationship

07:41.929 --> 07:44.965
that made him cranky,
which I found out after
I slept with him.

07:44.998 --> 07:46.967
Oh. Okay, good to know.
Mm-hmm. Anyway,

07:47.000 --> 07:49.236
now all of our hate is
reserved for "Vests,"

07:49.269 --> 07:51.739
the world's worst boss.

07:51.772 --> 07:53.507
Who's approaching.

07:53.541 --> 07:54.742
Hey, Scott.

07:57.277 --> 08:00.814
Uh, actually, I go
by Mr. Archuletta,
now that I'm manager.

08:00.848 --> 08:02.683
Seriously?
I told you.
You might want

08:02.716 --> 08:05.152
to shut it down, Lina--
because we have a problem.

08:05.185 --> 08:07.521
I know you've been stealing
liquor from the bar.
LINA: What?!

08:07.555 --> 08:09.957
I haven't stolen anything.
You were closing up last night

08:09.990 --> 08:12.526
when the bottles went missing,
and you were clearly drunk.

08:13.794 --> 08:15.963
(laughs):
Okay. I do not appreciate

08:15.996 --> 08:18.832
being accused of a crime
I did not commit,

08:18.866 --> 08:19.767
and I will use

08:19.800 --> 08:20.901
every legal recourse

08:20.934 --> 08:22.269
to fight these accusations,

08:22.302 --> 08:23.937
and then I will file
a counterclaim

08:23.971 --> 08:26.840
against you and the hotel,
and then you'll find yourself

08:26.874 --> 08:28.642
up to your eyeballs
in legal bills!

08:29.677 --> 08:30.978
I know it was you.

08:31.011 --> 08:33.080
Just figuring out
how to prove it.

08:33.113 --> 08:36.884
Okay, someone's
 Good Wife binge
 really paid off.

08:36.917 --> 08:37.951
I know.

08:37.985 --> 08:40.821
But, Jane... I didn't do it.

08:40.854 --> 08:43.823
So you weren't drinking at work.
Oh, of course
I was drinking at work.

08:43.857 --> 08:47.094
But ever since they
put in the new rules,
I bring my own booze.

08:47.127 --> 08:50.864
(groans): Oh...
I can't lose my job, Jane.

08:50.898 --> 08:54.134
Busboy Ben will definitely
go back to his girlfriend
if I'm not around.

08:54.167 --> 08:56.036
Okay. Calm down.

08:56.069 --> 08:58.271
(exhales)
We'll figure
it out.

08:58.305 --> 09:01.108
If you didn't do it, then
you're not losing your job.

09:01.141 --> 09:02.743
I have to go to work.

09:02.776 --> 09:04.745
No, you don't.

09:04.778 --> 09:06.580
I do.

09:07.380 --> 09:08.916
I feel okay.

09:08.949 --> 09:10.918
Where's my jacket?

09:10.951 --> 09:13.821
Oh. I got it.

09:16.123 --> 09:17.891
Thank you.
And thank you

09:17.925 --> 09:20.260
for taking care
of me last night.

09:21.962 --> 09:23.931
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
 To give some context--

09:23.964 --> 09:26.734
it's been exactly
 14 hours and 53 minutes

09:26.767 --> 09:29.837
since Luisa's ex-lover
 lay dead in front of her.

09:31.404 --> 09:33.641
(gasps)
No!

09:33.674 --> 09:35.142
Also...

09:35.175 --> 09:38.812
394 days
 since Luisa has had a drink.

09:38.846 --> 09:40.681
*

09:40.714 --> 09:43.216
Well... until last night.

09:43.250 --> 09:46.787
12 steps forward,
 one step back.

09:46.820 --> 09:48.388
And now this step.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.390
Jane, you'll recall,
 had decided to tell Rafael

09:50.423 --> 09:52.926
about Michael
 as soon as possible.

09:52.960 --> 09:55.095
(exhales)

09:55.128 --> 09:58.098
Shh, shh.
Mateo's still sleeping.

09:58.131 --> 10:00.100
Look what I got him
for his first swim lesson.

10:00.133 --> 10:01.935
So cute, right?

10:01.969 --> 10:03.937
Raf, I have to talk to you
about Michael.

10:03.971 --> 10:07.641
Oh, wow.
 So not even a little lead up?

10:07.675 --> 10:09.777
What about him?

10:09.810 --> 10:12.713
Well, he didn't want
to be around me or the baby

10:12.746 --> 10:14.982
while Rose was out there...

10:15.015 --> 10:16.684
but now...

10:16.717 --> 10:18.986
What?
Now...

10:20.220 --> 10:22.990
...she's gone and we're safe.

10:24.725 --> 10:26.326
He still loves me.

10:26.359 --> 10:28.228
And I still love him.

10:29.296 --> 10:30.864
No.

10:30.898 --> 10:31.865
What?

10:31.899 --> 10:34.434
Come on, anyone but him.

10:34.467 --> 10:37.137
I don't love anybody else.

10:37.170 --> 10:39.873
He punched me in the face.
I know.

10:39.907 --> 10:42.042
In front of Mateo.
And he feels bad.

10:42.075 --> 10:45.278
Oh, he feels bad?
Okay, so what I mean
is that he wants to apologize.

10:45.312 --> 10:48.949
He's different.
And you turned him in.
So that makes it okay?

10:48.982 --> 10:51.051
No, no, no.
That's not what I'm saying.
He's a bad guy.

10:51.084 --> 10:53.053
No, he's not.
Well, he's bad
for our family,

10:53.086 --> 10:54.955
and I want nothing to do
with him, okay?

10:54.988 --> 10:58.692
Are you serious?
What?

10:58.726 --> 11:01.028
Petra covered up for the fact
that her mom pushed

11:01.061 --> 11:03.063
my grandmother down the stairs,
and I threw her

11:03.096 --> 11:05.465
a freaking baby shower.
And now you're telling me

11:05.498 --> 11:07.968
you can't even have lunch
with Michael?
Fine.

11:08.001 --> 11:08.869
Let's all have lunch.

11:08.902 --> 11:11.204
Great! I look forward to it!

11:11.238 --> 11:13.406
Spoiler alert:

11:13.440 --> 11:14.908
I don't believe them.

11:19.980 --> 11:21.949
So, he agreed to lunch,
at least.

11:21.982 --> 11:23.450
And I use the term "agreed"
loosely.

11:23.483 --> 11:25.452
He definitely wasn't happy
about it.

11:25.485 --> 11:27.154
Yeah, well, it'd be weird
if he was.

11:27.187 --> 11:29.923
Yeah. That's true.
It's gonna be hard, obviously.

11:29.957 --> 11:32.325
I have to apologize.
Yeah.

11:32.359 --> 11:33.460
Any thoughts on what you'd say?

11:33.493 --> 11:34.862
Huh?
Because you can...

11:34.895 --> 11:35.996
try it out on me.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.931
No.
Michael.

11:37.965 --> 11:38.498
Your toast at Mark's wedding?

11:38.531 --> 11:40.167
Oh. Come on.

11:40.200 --> 11:40.968
What were your opening lines?
Let that go.

11:41.001 --> 11:41.835
Oh, yeah:
"For the longest time,

11:41.869 --> 11:45.072
"I thought Mark
was dating his sister."

11:45.105 --> 11:46.339
Who cuddles with their sister?

11:46.373 --> 11:47.841
(chuckles)

11:47.875 --> 11:49.943
Let's talk about this later,
okay?

11:49.977 --> 11:52.245
I love you.
Yeah, I love you, too.

11:52.279 --> 11:56.016
Anyone ever tell you you
got a goofy grin, Cordero?

11:56.049 --> 11:57.818
Hey. What are you doing here?

11:57.851 --> 11:58.952
You should be home
in bed.

